data.comment: The match has started at Stade Gaston Gerard.

In the minute 1, Throw-in for Dijon in their own half.
Free kick Rennes.
In Dijon-Prenois Rennes attack through Clement Grenier. The finish is off target, however.

Ball safe as Rennes is awarded a throw-in in their half.
Bastein Dechepy signals a free kick to Rennes just outside Dijon's area.

Bastein Dechepy signals a free kick to Rennes in their own half.
In the minute 12, Dijon are in shooting range from this free kick.
Corner awarded to Dijon.

Free kick for Dijon in their own half.

Romain Del Castillo is back on his feet again.
A throw-in for the away team on the opposite half.
In the minute 39, Dijon needs to be cautious. Rennes have an attacking throw-in.
Rennes have been awarded a corner by Bastein Dechepy.
Clement Grenier (Rennes) goes for goal but the shot is blocked by an alert defence.
In the minute 43, Rennes's Romain Del Castillo gets his shot away but it misses the target.
Goal kick for Dijon at Stade Gaston Gerard.
Dijon's Frederic Sammaritano breaks free at Stade Gaston Gerard. But the strike goes wide of the post.
In the minute 45, Ball goes out of play for a Rennes goal kick.
The fourth official's board shows 1 minutes, which will be added to the 1st half.
Rennes awarded a free kick in their own half.
In the minute 45, Bastein Dechepy blows to end the first-half.
The second-half is underway in Dijon-Prenois.

Throw-in for Rennes in the half of Dijon.
Free kick for Rennes in the half of Dijon.

Rennes make their second substitution with Yann Gboho replacing Martin Terrier.
In Dijon-Prenois a free kick has been awarded the away team.

Throw-in for Rennes in their own half.
Bastein Dechepy awards the home team a throw-in.

Free kick in a good position for Rennes!
Saturnin Allagbe (Dijon) gets a yellow card.

Corner awarded to Rennes.
Dijon have a goal kick.

Throw-in for Dijon in the half of Rennes.

A throw-in for the away team on the opposite half.

Dijon make their third substitution with Jordan Marie replacing Wesley Lautoa.

In the minute 81, Can Rennes get the ball into an attacking position from this throw-in in Dijon's half?
The away team replace Sehrou Guirassy with Adrien Hunou.

Throw-in for Rennes in the half of Dijon.
In the minute 82, Free kick for Rennes in the half of Dijon.
At Stade Gaston Gerard, Pape Diop has been yellow-carded for the home team.
Rennes drive into the zone and Flavien Tait is presented with a brilliant opportunity. But his strike hits the upright!
Bastein Dechepy awards Dijon a goal kick.
In the minute 85, It's getting dangerous! Free kick for Dijon close to the penalty box.
Dalbert for Rennes has been booked by Bastein Dechepy and receives a first yellow card.
Dijon have been awarded a corner by Bastein Dechepy.
In the minute 87, Free kick for Rennes in their own half.

Throw-in for Dijon close to the penalty box.
In the minute 88, In Dijon-Prenois a free kick has been awarded the home team.

Bastein Dechepy signals a free kick to Rennes in their own half.
Rennes have a goal kick.
Bastein Dechepy will wait an extra 4 minutes before blowing the whistle to end the 2nd half.
Throw-in for Dijon at Stade Gaston Gerard.
A throw-in for the away team on the opposite half.
Mama Balde gets his shot on target but fails to score for Dijon.
Dijon to take a throw-in in Rennes territory.
Can Rennes capitalize from this dangerous free kick?
In Dijon-Prenois, Daniele Rugani (Rennes) gets his head to the ball but the strike is cleared by an untiring defence.
It's 1-1 as the referee blows for full-time.
Jonas Martin is replacing Clement Grenier for the away team.
Mihai Dobre is on a sub for Eric Ebimbe for Dijon.
